      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De sapientia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e112">Neque hoc est sapere, quod intelligere, quia
              multi aeterna quidem sapiunt, sed haec intelligere nequaquam possunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e127">Sapienter illicita superat, qui didicerit etiam
              non uti concessis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e134">Augustinus, <title>de Libero arbitrio</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e142">Nemo sine sapientia beatus est: nemo enim beatus
              est nisi summo bono, quod in ea veritate, quam sapientiam vocamus, cernitur et
              tenetur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e149">Augustinus, <title>de Ordine disciplinae</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e157">Quisquis omnem philosophiam fugiendam putat,
              nihil nos vult aliud, quam non amare sapientiam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e165">Augustinus, <title>de Ordine disciplinae</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e173">Duplex est via quam sequimur: cum rerum nos
              obscuritas movet, aut ratione, aut certe auctoritate. Philosophia rationem
              promittit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e180">Augustinus, <title>de Ordine disciplinae</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e188">Tria sunt genera rerum, in quibus rationabile
              apparet; unum est in factis ad aliquem finem relatis; alterum in discendo; tertium in
              delectando. Primum nos admonet nihil temere facere; secundum, recte docere; ultimum,
              beate contemplari.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e195">Augustinus, <title>de Civitate Dei</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e203" source="http://scta.info/resource/adcd-l19-d1e3152">Non est vera sapientia, quae
              intentionem suam, in his quae prudenter discernit, gerit fortiter, cohibet
              temperanter, justeque distribuit, non ad illum dirigit finem, ubi erit Deus omnia in
              omnibus, aeternitate certa, et pace perfecta.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e210">Isidorus, in <title>Etymologiis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e218">Sapiens dictus est a
              <!--<i>-->sapore<!--</i>-->, quia sicut aptus est gustus ad discretionem saporis
              ciborum, sic sapiens ad dignoscentiam rerum atque causarum, quo unumquodque dignoscat,
              atque sensu veritatis discernat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e227">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e237" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e229">Isidorus, <title>de Summo bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e237">Nullus sapientiam Dei plene recipit, nisi qui se
              ab omnium abstrahere actionum cura contendit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e242">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e252" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e244">Ambrosius, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e252">Nihil peccare solius Dei est; sapientis est, et
              corrigere erratum, et poenitentiam agere peccati.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e258">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e268" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e260">Ambrosius, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e268">Sola est sapientia libera, quae divitibus
              pauperes praeficit, et quae servos propriis foenerari dominis facit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e273">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e283" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e275">Ambrosius, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e283">Ille vere sapit, cujus animus in Christo est, et
              cujus interior oculus erigitur ad superna.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e288">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e298" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e290">Bernardus, <title>de Consideratione</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e298">Quid prodest, si universum mundum lucreris, te
              unum perdens? Etsi sapiens aliis sis, deest tibi sapientia, si tibi non
              fueris.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e303">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e313" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e305">Bernardus, <title>super Cantica</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e313">Nescitis, quia angelus satanae multoties
              transfigurat se in angelum lucis? Sapientia est Deus, et vult se amari non solum
              dulciter, sed et sapienter.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e318">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e328" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e320">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e328">Sapiens videbit ubi victurus sit, cum quibus,
              quo, quid acturus: cogitat semper qualis vita, non quanta sit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e333">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e343" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e335">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e343">Sapiens omnia examinabit secum, quid acceperit,
              a quo, quantum, ubi, quemadmodum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e349">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e359" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e351">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e359">Sapiens bonorum rector, est malorum
              victor.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e364">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e374" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e366">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e374">Facere docet Philosophia, non dicere; et hoc
              exigit, ut ad legem suam quisque vivat, ne orationi vita dissentiat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e379">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e389" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e381">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e389">Rogo atque hortor, ut philosophiam in praecordia
              ima demittas, et experimentum profectus tui capias, non oratione, nec scripto, sed
              animi firmitate, cupiditatum diminutione, verba rebus proba.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e394">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e404" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e396">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e404">Affectator sapientiae adhaeret quidem in corpore
              suo; sed optima sui parte abest, et cogitationes suas ad sublimia intendit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e409">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e419" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e411">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e419">Ad philosophiam te confer, si vis salvus esse,
              si securus, si beatus, denique si vis esse, quod maximum est, liber.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-d1e424">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e434" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Rd1e426">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e44942-Qd1e434">Non est philosophia populare artificium, nec
              ostentatione paratum; nec in verbis, sed in rebus est; nec ad hoc adhibetur, ut cum
              aliqua oblectatione consumatur dies, ut dematur otio nausea: animum format et
              fabricat, vitam disponit, actiones regit, agenda et omittenda demonstrat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
